Server Creation = nodejs + Express
----------------------------------------

Basic Commands
--------------

1)Creation of the package.json - npm init
2)Creation of the node modules - npm i express (Installing of express)

Basic Steps
------------
1)creating a folder(Bankserver)
2)Create package.json
3)install express
4)Creating index.js
5)import express inside the index.js
6)Create an app using the express
7)setup port number
8)Resolving http request
      Get - To get the data
      Post - To post the data
      Put - update data partialy
      patch - update the data completely
      Delete - To delete the data completely

9)HTP Response Code
     1xx -Information
     2xx -succcessful
     3xx -redirection   
     4xx -clind error
     5xx -server error

10)JWT token
    install JWT - npm i jsonwebtoken
    To create a token -sign()

11)Middleware

   it comes in  the middle of the request and the response cycle of the nodejs exicution process

   req,res,next

   1)Application Specific Middleware - for entire application 
   2)Router specific middleware - For token verification - verify()


12)Database integration
      1)Install mongoose - npm i mongoose

13)Asyncronous function resolving - promise

      1)REsolve state - .then()
      2)Reject state - catch()

14)CORS - cross origin resource sharing

        instal cors - npm i cors

15) Asyncronous call - RxJs -(Reactive Extension for Javascript)

JS - promise
TS -RxJs(Library)

         1)Observable
                 a)resolved - Subcribe()
                 b)reject - catch